Good question! The checkpoints are indeed chained together - each checkpoint references the previous checkpoint's hash. This is an important part of the design.

Should I add hash references to the diagram? This would show:
- Checkpoint N-1 has hash H_{N-1}
- Checkpoint N references prev_hash = H_{N-1}
- Checkpoint N+1 references prev_hash = H_N

This would make the diagram more technically accurate but also more complex. Let me propose both options to Allan.

